BOOK: Plasma

MATERIAL: Cold_plasma

TITLE: Plasma_geometry

QUESTION: property
VALUE: cold_plasma
STATE: HIDDEN

QUESTION: Geometry_extrapolation#CB#(Flat_1D,Curved,Full_3D,Tensor)
VALUE: Flat
HELP: Plasma geometry extrapolation types:\n \n- 'Flat_1D': a 1D measurement line is read from the files specified in the 'ne_file_path' and 'Be_file_path' fields. \n    The 1D line is extrapolated into the 3D geometry by extrusion in the toroidal direction and with a curvature \n    in the poloidal direction defined by the 'Poloidal_ne_curvature' and 'Poloidal_Be_curvature' fields. The first \n    point of the 1D measurement line is placed at the coordinates specified in the 'L1_00_XYZ' fields.\n    The values of 'ne' and 'Be' outside the defined line will correspond to those at the endpoints of the line.\n \n- 'Curved': a 1D measurement line is read from the files specified in the 'ne_file_path' and 'Be_file_path' fields. \n    The 1D line is extrapolated into the 3D geometry by extrusion, applying a poloidal curvature defined by \n    the 'Poloidal_ne_curvature' and 'Poloidal_Be_curvature' fields, and a toroidal curvature determined by the \n    distance to the tokamak centre. The tokamak centre coordinates are specified in the 'TK_00_XYZ' fields. \n    The first point of the 1D measurement line is placed at the coordinates defined in the 'L1_00_XYZ' fields.\n    The values of 'ne' and 'Be' outside the defined line will correspond to those at the endpoints of the line.\n \n- 'Full_3D': pointwise nodal 3D distributions are read from the files specified in the fields 'ne_file_path' and \n    'Be_file_path'. The density and field distributions are applied directly to the 3D geometry node-by-node. \n    The folder '\\Documents\\Plasma_Files' contains practical examples of Python scripts to transform EQDSK \n    equilibrium plasma files into the required format.\n \n- 'Tensor': a permittivity tensor defined in the binary file 'Tensor_K_CPGE.bin' is applied to the mesh nodes.\n    This tensor make use of the density and magnetic field 3D data specified in the files 'ne_file_path' and \n    'Be_file_path'. The tensor components must be relative to the vacuum permittivity and defined in the Be \n    field coordinate system. The tensor file must be saved in the problem folder. An example of the required \n    file format can be found in the '\\Documents\\Plasma_Files\\Python_Scripts' directory.\n
QUESTION: Poloidal_ne_curvature
VALUE: 0.0
HELP: Poloidal curvature applied to 'ne' density profile in the 'Flat_1D' and 'Curved' modes.\nThe centre of curvature is located at a distance equal to the 'Poloidal_ne_curvature' from \nthe first point of the 1D measurement line. The first point of the 1D measurement line \nis located at the coordinates specified in the 'L1_00_XYZ' fields.
QUESTION: Poloidal_Be_curvature
VALUE: 0.0
HELP: Poloidal curvature applied to the 'Be' field profile in the 'Flat_1D' and 'Curved' modes.\nThe centre of curvature is located at a distance equal to the 'Poloidal_Be_curvature' from \nthe first point of the 1D measurement line. The first point of the 1D measurement line \nis located at the coordinates specified in the 'L1_00_XYZ' fields.
QUESTION: ___#CB#(_)
VALUE:
QUESTION: L1_00_X
VALUE: 0.0
HELP: X coordinate of the first point of the 1D measurement line.
QUESTION: L1_00_Y
VALUE: 0.0
HELP: Y coordinate of the first point of the 1D measurement line.
QUESTION: L1_00_Z
VALUE: 0.0
HELP: Z coordinate of the first point of the 1D measurement line.
QUESTION: ____#CB#(_)
VALUE: 
QUESTION: TK_00_X
VALUE: 0.0
HELP: X coordinate of the centre of the tokamak.
QUESTION: TK_00_Y
VALUE: 0.0
HELP: Y coordinate of the centre of the tokamak.
QUESTION: TK_00_Z
VALUE: 0.0
HELP: Z coordinate of the centre of the tokamak.
QUESTION: _____#CB#(_)
VALUE:      
QUESTION: TK_axis_X
VALUE: 0.0
HELP: X component of the main axis of the tokamak.
QUESTION: TK_axis_Y
VALUE: 0.0
HELP: Y component of the main axis of the tokamak.
QUESTION: TK_axis_Z
VALUE: 0.0
